In the 1970s Budd Lewis was a prolific writer for Warren Publishing. He wrote more than 150 stories for Creepy, Eerie and Vampirella.

Lewis has also worked as a storybook director, animator, screenwriter, film designer and in special effects.
name: Budd Lewis

deck: Erica Schultz is an American comics writer and the co-creator of M3. Her most notable works are Revenge: The Secret Origin of Emily Thorne for Marvel Comics, and The Unauthorized Biography of Winston Churchill with artist Claire Connelly. She is also a writer on 2015's Vertigo Quarterly: SFX #1 as well as one of Gail Simone's hand-picked writers for Dynamite's Swords of Sorrow crossover event.
description:
Erica Schultz is an American comics writer and the co-creator of crime series M3, the winner of the "Best Comic Book" award at the 2012 Burbank International Film Festival.

Her most notable works as of late are the original graphic novel Revenge: The Secret Origin of Emily Thorne for Marvel Comics, Dynamite's Swords of Sorrow: Masquerade & Kato one-shot (co-written with G. Willow Wilson) and the Swords of Sorrow: Black Sparrow & Lady Zorro one-shot, both part of Gail Simone's all-female crossover event. She also wrote The Unauthorized Biography of Winston Churchill: A Documentary and Cheese: A Love Story with artist Claire Connelly. Schultz wrote "Pop Goes The World" in 2015's Vertigo Quarterly: SFX #1. Schultz also serves as letterer on all the Swords of Sorrow books.

She provided artistic support for Neal Adams on The New Avengers 16.1, The First X-Men, Batman Odyssey, and Blood.
name: Erica Schultz

Career

Natasha Allegri is probably best known for her work on the Adventure Time franchise, having worked as a storyboard artist and writer for the animated series. She also created Fionna, the gender swapped version of Finn, and sings the alternate theme sing for Fionna's episodes.
name: Natasha Allegri
